/*
SVG Icons

The SVG icons are specified in a separate file and can be included via a an
Angular directive built for this purpose.

The markup below which makes use of the object tag is used only for listing
the icons and not for actually displaying them.

The first 2 examples are examples of actual usage. You can either specify a scale,
which is a multiplier on the base icon dimensions or you can specify dimensions,
which should respect the ratio.

See cf_icon_directive.js or /app/svg/contentful_icons for more info.

Markup:
p
  cf-icon(name="contentTypes" scale="2")
  img(width="50" height="50" src="/app/images/contentful_icons.svg#nav-entries")
p
  cf-icon(name="contentTypes" width="50" height="50")
  img(width="30" height="30" src="/app/images/contentful_icons.svg#nav-entries")

Styleguide 10.1
*/

